This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the use of translations to learn linguistic properties and semantic representations. It also involves the use of machine translation models to find language-independent meaning representations. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of neural machine translation models to learn from massive amounts of data. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to learn about language relationships and create language spaces. 

It could also belong to cs.DL (Deep Learning) as it involves the use of neural networks to learn from data. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it involves the use of large corpora and complex models to learn about language relationships.
